I think I have an convergence problem with my monitor because looking
at white on black characters through a magnifing glass the letters
are green on the bottom pixels and red on the top.  I bought 
some software to check the focus,convergence and geometric distortion
hopefully making it obvious when I take this thing back.

My question is if the pixels are about .3mm and the convergence spec
is .3mm this seems to me that it would be in spec for all the color
beams to be off by a whole pixel which I believe would make for some
pretty fuzzy 8 pixel wide characters. 

The first monitor I took back had a slight rotation problem (but it
had a better picture quality).  I called Samsung and they told me the
spec for rotation which at its maximum is too much in my opinion
(Surely the most primitive way to insure proper rotation would just
to rotate the tube alittle).  The distributer of course took it back
anyway.

It seems to me the only way to buy a large high-res monitor is to
test it with your equipment (at 1280x1024 not 640x350) before you
leave the store!

